74
00:05:44,828 --> 00:05:47,827
"Kimie Muto (30), Shohei Muto (33)" -You must be tired from the long trip.

75
00:05:47,828 --> 00:05:49,727
Well, hello.

76
00:05:49,728 --> 00:05:53,127
We look forward to staying here, Mr. Muto.

77
00:05:53,128 --> 00:05:56,027
Yes, we hope you get to relax here.

78
00:05:56,028 --> 00:05:59,327
Well them, I'll be off to sterilize the premises.

79
00:05:59,328 --> 00:06:01,428
I'm counting on you, Mr. Mouri.

80
00:06:05,028 --> 00:06:07,527
It's okay, Mr. Mouri.

81
00:06:07,528 --> 00:06:10,427
It's already been sterilized inside.

82
00:06:10,428 --> 00:06:12,327
Chief Dobashi?

83
00:06:12,328 --> 00:06:14,927
You're here too, Mr. Dobashi?

84
00:06:14,928 --> 00:06:17,527
I heard that you were unusually taking time off,

85
00:06:17,528 --> 00:06:20,027
so I thought you were out with your family.

86
00:06:20,028 --> 00:06:23,328
If I remember correctly, you have a daughter?

87
00:06:24,428 --> 00:06:25,827
Don't worry.

88
00:06:25,828 --> 00:06:28,528
I'm getting along fine with my daughter.

89
00:06:29,828 --> 00:06:32,027
Well, what a coincidence!

90
00:06:32,028 --> 00:06:34,727
I have a daughter too.

91
00:06:34,728 --> 00:06:37,627
Mr. Mouri, today is also your graduation exam day

92
00:06:37,628 --> 00:06:39,627
from Dobashi Security Guard Agency, you know.

93
00:06:39,628 --> 00:06:42,627
Oh, yes, indeed.

94
00:06:42,628 --> 00:06:44,627
Talk about stressful.

95
00:06:44,628 --> 00:06:48,627
How reassuring to have two good men looking out for me.

96
00:06:48,628 --> 00:06:50,527
I feel like a princess.

97
00:06:50,528 --> 00:06:53,427
Yeah, but a princess way past her prime I'd say.

98
00:06:53,428 --> 00:06:55,827
Reina.

99
00:06:55,828 --> 00:06:59,327
Then, why don't you look after Princess Reina, Mr. Dobashi?

100
00:06:59,328 --> 00:07:02,528
I feel safe as long as Mr. Mouri's with me.

101
00:07:05,128 --> 00:07:07,128
Come on, dad.

102
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:12,027
I'm perfectly fine with sweetie Kusumoto, you see.

103
00:07:12,028 --> 00:07:14,627
Oh no... I'm not a bodyguard.

104
00:07:14,628 --> 00:07:15,928
I'm just joking.

105
00:07:18,828 --> 00:07:23,027
Reina's famous for being a troublemaker, right?

106
00:07:23,028 --> 00:07:26,127
Yes, I hear she's always fighting at the location sites.

107
00:07:26,128 --> 00:07:28,527
-Moreover... -We're in the same agency,

108
00:07:28,528 --> 00:07:31,127
and yet are like cats and dogs.

109
00:07:31,128 --> 00:07:33,427
That's famous too.

110
00:07:33,428 --> 00:07:36,327
But, I may be the problem rather than her.

111
00:07:36,328 --> 00:07:38,727
I don't get along with anyone here,

112
00:07:38,728 --> 00:07:41,827
I wonder why nobody likes me.

113
00:07:41,828 --> 00:07:45,927
Is it because I try too hard although it's not a drama?

114
00:07:45,928 --> 00:07:48,127
Am I taking too long?

115
00:07:48,128 --> 00:07:49,527
No... That's not it...

116
00:07:49,528 --> 00:07:52,527
This program wouldn't exist without you, Ryo.

117
00:07:52,528 --> 00:07:54,527
I heard, Kushizaki.

118
00:07:54,528 --> 00:07:56,227
Rumor that the program'll be cancelled.

119
00:07:56,228 --> 00:07:58,427
And that the ratings are low too.

120
00:07:58,428 --> 00:08:01,828
No... Rumors are nothing more than rumors.

121
00:08:03,528 --> 00:08:07,227
I'm sorry if you lose your jobs.

122
00:08:07,228 --> 00:08:09,228
It's all because of me.

123
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:19,827
I mean, she's making the most out of all of us.

124
00:08:19,828 --> 00:08:22,427
She's paid more than her skills and time are worth.

125
00:08:22,428 --> 00:08:23,428
That's what it is...

126
00:08:23,429 --> 00:08:26,428
Cool it. Isokawa, come on.

127
00:08:27,228 --> 00:08:28,927
-This voice? -It's Reina.

128
00:08:28,928 --> 00:08:30,427
What do you mean it's already sterilized?

129
00:08:30,428 --> 00:08:31,928
It can't be!

130
00:08:38,828 --> 00:08:39,928
Are you all right?

131
00:08:40,728 --> 00:08:42,528
What? What the...

132
00:08:47,928 --> 00:08:49,328
I've had it!

133
00:08:51,628 --> 00:08:54,527
What's the matter, Reina?

134
00:08:54,528 --> 00:08:55,928
Maybe it's that?

135
00:09:00,828 --> 00:09:02,327
I'm so sorry...

136
00:09:02,328 --> 00:09:04,627
There are a lot of stray cats out here.

137
00:09:04,628 --> 00:09:07,128
I'll clean the room up again right away.

138
00:09:07,928 --> 00:09:10,627
Hey, you know it, right, Kusumoto?

139
00:09:10,628 --> 00:09:13,827
That I really can't handle this.

140
00:09:13,828 --> 00:09:15,427
Allergic to cats.

141
00:09:15,428 --> 00:09:16,627
I'm sorry.

142
00:09:16,628 --> 00:09:20,527
I did tell Mr. Mouri about you too, Reina, but...

143
00:09:20,528 --> 00:09:22,527
No, it's my mistake.

144
00:09:22,528 --> 00:09:26,027
I should've left everything up to Mr. Mouri.

145
00:09:26,028 --> 00:09:27,327
I'm sorry.

146
00:09:27,328 --> 00:09:29,627
What? Is something wrong?

147
00:09:29,628 --> 00:09:30,827
Not really...

148
00:09:30,828 --> 00:09:33,327
I'm not a Maru-whatever,

149
00:09:33,328 --> 00:09:37,128
