205
00:13:10,304 --> 00:13:12,803
How frightening.

206
00:13:12,804 --> 00:13:15,603
Mr. Dobashi, you have a phone call.

207
00:13:15,604 --> 00:13:17,704
It must be the results of the investigation.

208
00:13:18,304 --> 00:13:19,504
Investigation?

209
00:13:30,904 --> 00:13:35,303
Mr. Kushizaki, please send in the two extras.

210
00:13:35,304 --> 00:13:36,503
Okay.

211
00:13:36,504 --> 00:13:39,303
Conan, Ran, you're on.

212
00:13:39,304 --> 00:13:40,304
Yes, sir.

213
00:13:40,304 --> 00:13:41,304
Let's go.

214
00:13:42,404 --> 00:13:44,204
What's that?

215
00:13:53,604 --> 00:13:54,804
What's happening?

216
00:13:58,004 --> 00:13:59,603
What a dense fog.

217
00:13:59,604 --> 00:14:01,803
Is everyone okay?

218
00:14:01,804 --> 00:14:04,603
This is Arimura! The oars aren't working.

219
00:14:04,604 --> 00:14:07,003
And we lost sight of Ryo and Reina.

220
00:14:07,004 --> 00:14:08,904
What?

221
00:14:10,204 --> 00:14:12,903
Mr. Mouri! Confirm whether the Marutai is safe!

222
00:14:12,904 --> 00:14:15,403
But my oars aren't working either...

223
00:14:15,404 --> 00:14:17,003
I can't see her.

224
00:14:17,004 --> 00:14:18,803
Dad! Are you okay?

225
00:14:18,804 --> 00:14:21,803
Leave it to me! I give you my word, I'll keep her safe.

226
00:14:21,804 --> 00:14:25,303
Hold it, I just received some unbelievable inspection results.

227
00:14:25,304 --> 00:14:26,903
On this case we're handling,

228
00:14:26,904 --> 00:14:30,403
she could've made all this up.

229
00:14:30,404 --> 00:14:33,103
It seems that an informal decision of laying her off

230
00:14:33,104 --> 00:14:35,203
from the agency has been in process.

231
00:14:35,204 --> 00:14:37,603
And it seems she caught on to this...

232
00:14:37,604 --> 00:14:41,103
So, she conjured up a topic that would interest the mass media.

233
00:14:41,104 --> 00:14:42,803
No way.

234
00:14:42,804 --> 00:14:45,703
But the worst of it all, is that it seems she thinks

235
00:14:45,704 --> 00:14:49,403
that Reina has caught on to this too.

236
00:14:49,404 --> 00:14:51,203
Don't tell me that because of this?

237
00:14:51,204 --> 00:14:53,903
Ryo's going to kill Reina?

238
00:14:53,904 --> 00:14:55,303
Wait, Conan!

239
00:14:55,304 --> 00:14:56,704
I'll row the boat!

240
00:14:59,404 --> 00:15:02,603
No good. I can't work the oars...

241
00:15:02,604 --> 00:15:04,803
Do you see anything, Conan?

242
00:15:04,804 --> 00:15:06,704
Nope. Nothing at all...

243
00:15:09,204 --> 00:15:10,903
What's this sound?

244
00:15:10,904 --> 00:15:12,104
What was that?

245
00:15:17,004 --> 00:15:18,104
This sound?

246
00:15:20,004 --> 00:15:22,703
No good, we're being swept away.

247
00:15:22,704 --> 00:15:24,803
I see! I got it.

248
00:15:24,804 --> 00:15:26,904
Conan? What's that?

249
00:15:37,804 --> 00:15:40,704
Darn, I'm being swept away by the wind.

250
00:15:42,104 --> 00:15:43,204
That's...

251
00:15:49,504 --> 00:15:50,704
That's...

252
00:15:55,004 --> 00:15:57,303
This is Ryo's...

253
00:15:57,304 --> 00:15:58,704
The other is the film crews'...

254
00:16:03,104 --> 00:16:06,504
Ryo, where are you?

255
00:16:12,104 --> 00:16:13,404
Reina?

256
00:16:15,104 --> 00:16:17,203
She's just passed out.

257
00:16:17,204 --> 00:16:19,304
Don't tell me that Ryo...

258
00:16:25,704 --> 00:16:28,403
Everybody got washed up here like us.

259
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:31,103
Wait over here, Ran, since it's dangerous.

260
00:16:31,104 --> 00:16:32,603
No, Conan!

261
00:16:32,604 --> 00:16:34,004
I'm coming with you.

262
00:16:42,304 --> 00:16:43,304
Ryo?

263
00:16:43,305 --> 00:16:45,503
Stay away, Mr. Mouri!

264
00:16:45,504 --> 00:16:47,103
Don't tell me... Just as I thought...

265
00:16:47,104 --> 00:16:48,203
Don't move!

266
00:16:48,204 --> 00:16:49,404
What?

267
00:17:17,204 --> 00:17:18,204
Dad?

268
00:17:18,205 --> 00:17:19,803
Are you all right, Pops?

269
00:17:19,804 --> 00:17:21,403
Hide, both of you!

270
00:17:21,404 --> 00:17:22,803
Mr. Mouri...

271
00:17:22,804 --> 00:17:24,603
Who the heck was that?

272
00:17:24,604 --> 00:17:26,503
Where's Reina? Where is she?

273
00:17:26,504 --> 00:17:30,103
What? Could that have been her?

274
00:17:30,104 --> 00:17:33,203
She pretended to be passed out and after I left.

275
00:17:33,204 --> 00:17:34,903
That's not it.

276
00:17:34,904 --> 00:17:36,703
No, not possible.

277
00:17:36,704 --> 00:17:39,703
That cat-hater could never make it this far.

278
00:17:39,704 --> 00:17:40,803
More importantly,

279
00:17:40,804 --> 00:17:44,704
how'd you know all the boats would be washed up here?

280
00:17:46,604 --> 00:17:49,903
Oh, so that's the story.

281
00:17:49,904 --> 00:17:52,803
Ryo, will you trust me?

282
00:17:52,804 --> 00:17:56,203
Of course, you're my bodyguard.

283
00:17:56,204 --> 00:17:58,704
Okay, then.

284
00:18:00,504 --> 00:18:04,403
Ryo, hide behind that big tree.

285
00:18:04,404 --> 00:18:07,304
No, Pops! You didn't sterilize yet.

286
00:18:15,604 --> 00:18:16,704
What the...

287
00:18:23,604 --> 00:18:24,704
Mr. Dobashi?

288
00:18:26,504 --> 00:18:28,303
Dad, are you all right?

289
00:18:28,304 --> 00:18:30,203
You did it, Pops!

290
00:18:30,204 --> 00:18:33,703
Mr. Dobashi, you checked beforehand, didn't you?

291
00:18:33,704 --> 00:18:35,903
The direction the wind would blow if there is to be a fog,

292
00:18:35,904 --> 00:18:37,603
the movement of the waves,

293
00:18:37,604 --> 00:18:40,503
or where we would all land if we were swept away by the wind...

294
00:18:40,504 --> 00:18:42,604
In other words, you sterilized the place.

295
00:18:43,804 --> 00:18:46,503
You beat everyone here on a motorboat

296
00:18:46,504 --> 00:18:48,703
that you probably got ready beforehand

297
00:18:48,704 --> 00:18:53,003
that wouldn't be affected by the wind or the waves.

298
00:18:53,004 --> 00:18:56,103
So, the sound we heard was that of a motorboat.

299
00:18:56,104 --> 00:18:59,003
You did all this to kill Ryo.

300
00:18:59,004 --> 00:19:00,403
You wanted to make it look like Ryo killed Reina,

301
00:19:00,404 --> 00:19:03,203
then killed me as well because I tried to stop her,

302
00:19:03,204 --> 00:19:05,804
and then finally she kills herself.

303
00:19:07,304 --> 00:19:10,103
And, you were saying something about an investigation, weren't you?

304
00:19:10,104 --> 00:19:12,103
That was indeed something you made up.

305
00:19:12,104 --> 00:19:14,303
You asked someone at your company

306
00:19:14,304 --> 00:19:17,003
to call you at a pre-set time.

307
00:19:17,004 --> 00:19:19,103
The contents didn't matter.

308
00:19:19,104 --> 00:19:22,503
I can easily check on it and confirm!

309
00:19:22,504 --> 00:19:24,903
Oh, there you are, everyone.

310
00:19:24,904 --> 00:19:28,904
It's good that we landed but, we got lost in the fog...

311
00:19:29,304 --> 00:19:32,003
I heard something that sounded like a gun shot?

312
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:34,203
Did something happen?

313
00:19:34,204 --> 00:19:36,103
What now, Mr. Dobashi?

314
00:19:36,104 --> 00:19:39,904
It's hard to silence as many people as this, you know?

315
00:19:41,904 --> 00:19:44,403
It was last month.

316
00:19:44,404 --> 00:19:46,803
That my daughter tried out for an audition for a drama

317
00:19:46,804 --> 00:19:48,603
and was dropped.

318
00:19:48,604 --> 00:19:50,403
She was so depressed,

319
00:19:50,404 --> 00:19:53,203
she attempted suicide the following day.

320
00:19:53,204 --> 00:19:57,003
The judge at that time was her.

321
00:19:57,004 --> 00:20:01,803
I wanted to take revenge for my daughter, as her father.

322
00:20:01,804 --> 00:20:05,004
Wait, that wasn't me.

323
00:20:06,304 --> 00:20:08,403
I wasn't feeling well that day,

324
00:20:08,404 --> 00:20:10,003
so I had someone else take my place.

325
00:20:10,004 --> 00:20:11,004
As judge.

326
00:20:11,005 --> 00:20:12,303
Who was it?

327
00:20:12,304 --> 00:20:14,603
Me.

328
00:20:14,604 --> 00:20:16,103
Enough, already.

329
00:20:16,104 --> 00:20:18,503
I was dodging the kitties and fell.

330
00:20:18,504 --> 00:20:20,803
I fainted!

331
00:20:20,804 --> 00:20:25,003
I mean, I can't stand the itchiness.

332
00:20:25,004 --> 00:20:26,803
You're the one who dropped my daughter.

333
00:20:26,804 --> 00:20:29,903
So... If you're going to kill anyone, it should be me.

334
00:20:29,904 --> 00:20:33,803
You shouldn't make a mistake, you know?

335
00:20:33,804 --> 00:20:38,103
Your daughter misses you and wants to see you.

336
00:20:38,104 --> 00:20:40,203
Reina's been visiting the hospital to see her

337
00:20:40,204 --> 00:20:42,903
at least once every two days.

338
00:20:42,904 --> 00:20:44,904
You knew?

339
00:20:47,004 --> 00:20:50,603
It's just like you, so different from me.

340
00:20:50,604 --> 00:20:54,204
But, you didn't even know about it, Mr. Dobashi.

341
00:20:58,904 --> 00:21:02,003
You get along fine with your daughter?

342
00:21:02,004 --> 00:21:05,303
And this is what you do? Killing people?

343
00:21:05,304 --> 00:21:07,003
You didn't do it for you daughter.

344
00:21:07,004 --> 00:21:09,703
You did it only to attain self-satisfaction.

345
00:21:09,704 --> 00:21:11,703
Didn't you do this just so that you could prove to yourself

346
00:21:11,704 --> 00:21:15,404
that you were being her father?

347
00:21:20,804 --> 00:21:22,103
You may be a bodyguard,

348
00:21:22,104 --> 00:21:24,803
but you're a failure as a father.

349
00:21:24,804 --> 00:21:28,303
Well, I can't talk either, but...

350
00:21:28,304 --> 00:21:29,604
Dad.

351
00:21:31,904 --> 00:21:35,103
Right, the same goes for you, Mr. Mouri.

352
00:21:35,104 --> 00:21:36,603
You're a failure as a bodyguard.

353
00:21:36,604 --> 00:21:38,603
You used me as decoy.

354
00:21:38,604 --> 00:21:41,403
Well... That was...

355
00:21:41,404 --> 00:21:43,103
You're fired as of today.

356
00:21:43,104 --> 00:21:46,403
Go back to where you belong!

357
00:21:46,404 --> 00:21:47,804
Yes.

358
00:21:51,204 --> 00:21:53,904
Thank you, Mr. Detective.

359
00:23:16,804 --> 00:23:18,903
"Mouri Detective Agency."

360
00:23:18,904 --> 00:23:20,003
"Ryo Haneki Retires!"

361
00:23:20,004 --> 00:23:24,003
Ryo's going to go independent and become president of a company.

362
00:23:24,004 --> 00:23:25,703
It seems Reina, who moved agencies,

363
00:23:25,704 --> 00:23:26,903
is going to be the first actress

364
00:23:26,904 --> 00:23:29,303
with an exclusive contract at Ryo's agency.

365
00:23:29,304 --> 00:23:31,603
This is it...

366
00:23:31,604 --> 00:23:34,203
Weren't you fired, Dad?

367
00:23:34,204 --> 00:23:36,403
I'm going to accumulate more results

368
00:23:36,404 --> 00:23:39,403
and become Yoko's exclusive bodyguard.

369
00:23:39,404 --> 00:23:41,504
So that's what you're after.

370
00:23:42,604 --> 00:23:44,604
The old man never learns.

371
00:23:45,804 --> 00:23:53,603
"Next Episode."

372
00:23:53,604 --> 00:23:54,804
This is bad!

373
00:24:02,004 --> 00:24:03,703
Hey, what's going on?

374
00:24:03,704 --> 00:24:05,903
Ayumi's been kidnapped!

375
00:24:05,904 --> 00:24:07,704
I'll go after him!

376
00:24:10,204 --> 00:24:15,804
Next Conan, "The Secret of the Disappearance of the Young Wife"

